    "what_description": "Rosmarinus officinalis is a perennial evergreen shrub native to the Mediterranean region, belonging to the family Lamiaceae. It has woody stems, 30-100 cm tall, with needle-like leaves 2-3 cm long, aromatic and dark green, arranged oppositely on the stem. The leaves are elliptical, entire and pointed, with a short petiole. The flowers are small, blue, and fragrant, in axillary whorls, arranged in a spike-like inflorescence, 2-4 cm long, and are pollinated by bees. The fruit is a small, brown nut, 2-3 mm long, containing one seed.",
